# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for the Moonlab concurrency lane.
#
# The Homebrew/LLVM libomp shipped on developer machines is NOT built with
# the Archer TSan-annotation layer, so TSan cannot observe the happens-before
# established by OpenMP barriers/reductions and reports false positives on the
# runtime's own internal state.  Suppress anything originating inside the
# OpenMP runtime library.  This does NOT hide races whose accesses are in
# Moonlab code (gates.c / state.c / grover.c / parallel_ops.c / scheduler.c);
# those still fire.
#
# To validate the OpenMP regions WITHOUT these suppressions, run on a Linux
# CI runner with an Archer-instrumented libomp (see .github/workflows/tsan.yml)
# where the barrier annotations make the false positives disappear for real.

called_from_lib:libomp.dylib
called_from_lib:libomp.so
race:__kmp
race:__gomp
race:kmp_
deadlock:__kmp
